cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.SI

The paper discusses a security vulnerability in smartwatches and proposes a system to extract and infer passwords entered on these devices. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The proposed system uses deep neural networks for inference, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the potential privacy implications of this vulnerability, which falls under the category of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
